This paper deals with the issue of machine bias in AI, specifically in machine translation. It discusses the tendency of Google Translate to default to male pronouns, particularly in fields with unbalanced gender distribution such as STEM jobs. This falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves statistical analysis (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.CY) to collect and analyze data. Additionally, it touches on the topic of fairness and ethics in AI (cs.SD).
